<br>
&quot;Wow, did a little looking, and the pet was backstabbing for 241! Good job Warrior, keep that mob back to the pet we kill fast!&quot;<br>
<br>
I'm feeling all good about myself, handing out rods to the cleric, making mobs easier to slow/mezz with sini, when all of a sudden the 63 monk pipes up.<br>
<br>
&quot;Your pet parsed 87.5 DPS that last fight Baervon.&quot;<br>
<br>
*insert picture of my jaw hitting the floor*<br>
<br>
&quot;Wow, it did? Check Jabober out *flex*&quot;<br>
<br>
Bear in mind that's MELEE DMG. No procs. No DS. No nukes.<br>
<br>
The 63 monk then said &quot;It is outdamaging every other melee here except me in fact.&quot; The 63 monk had something obscene like 137 AAs and had offtanked adds, he was pretty damn uber. The 61 monk looked normal-ish to me, was swinging some 2handed hammer, the warrior had that skull topped basher and something else, I dunno, they all looked pretty good to me. To the crux of the matter, what do you think the parties response was?<br>
<br>
61 monk - &quot;Damn I need to work on some AAs, that's crazay nice for a pet.&quot;<br>
63 monk - &quot;I love mages, they deal SOOOO much dmg.&quot;<br>
Cleric - &quot;Daaaaaamn, go mages.&quot;<br>
warrior - No comment I think he was a mute he didn't say much the whole damn group.<br>
Enchanter - &quot;Yeah I think I'll have to group with more good mages from now on&quot;<br>
<br>
No nerf pets yell. No jealousy. Just happiness that they got to group with a solid DPS machine like MOI. And assurances that in the future, they'd look at mages. I think this is great. Mages finally starting to get a fair shake in things. POSITIVE image. Wow, what a change.<br>
<br>
Now for all you people who think saying stuff like this gets us nerfed, shut the hell up. I was getting less med time running around positioning the pet, and warrior had to work a little too, so this isn't automatic by any means. My nuking was limited to one FBoT and one SoFB to finish off the mob, any more nuking and I'd lose mana. So I dealt what, 3500 in nukes per mobs while pet whaled away on it. No idea what total DPS on a per mob basis was and we were not in a high uptime group, we killed one puller ran and got another. I'd say 15 second downtime after each kill.<br>
<br>
That's not the point tho. Point is, we are GETTING BETTER PRESS. And it's thru totally random people, like the monk who just happened to want to parse my pet. Pet was equipped with a Muzzle and BO5 by the way. I just got the Dark Tower game I bid for on Ebay via Fed Ex so I'm gonna have to end this little report on pets, and their affect on the mage image. <br>
<br>
Be proud! We FINALLY get our just desserts!<br>
<br>
Baervon<br>
Mage since before our pets had casting effects<br>
Quellious server<br>
